  <discussion>The degenerate peristome is the major distinguishing trait of Tortula plinthobia, which is widespread but endemic to the flora area.  It is doubtfully distinct from T. muralis at the species level, and the similar gametophyte coupled with the flattened, weakly twisted 16 teeth, each divided into 2 branches, indicates that this peristome type, also associated with the old genus Desmatodon, is not in itself a trait implying taxonomic distinction at the genus level.</discussion>
